				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just some backround: i am in my 44th season, just so you all know my spell capabilities.  I continuely get told by everyone but rangers to snare mobs both in ldon and hunting outside.  Never by any means root them?  I just don't understand, I pull with snare they get close and i feel i should root them...  Makes sense to me no running mobs.  Had one run the other nite in an adventure, then got yelled at for not rooting, only response was "you told me never root, hence spell isnt memmed."  Am i wrong or what? Let me know all wise ones.</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
