			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">True, rooted mobs won't run, but they <span style="font-style: italic">will</span> continue to fight after they would otherwise have started running-as a result, you end up having to take more damage from them than you would otherwise. Also, though snared mobs will run, the snare combined with the natural speed decrease that their low hitpoints is giving them makes sure that they don't get anywhere fast. Also, since root isn't generally necesarry (unless you're buying some time to back off and heal/buff/DoT), it costs a lot less mana in the long run to just use snare.
<br />

<br />
Of course, it depends on situation. If you're in a tight spot with a lot of potential adds, then it's probably worth rooting the mob just to make sure you don't have to deal with any more than you want to. Keep in mind though that root can break, whereas snare is much harder to get rid of. Especially if you have a nuker in your group, the root doesn't stand a chance of sticking.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=886284" target="_blank" class="postlink">Iainin Eastwind</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.quellious.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Quellious Server</a></span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
