				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Geminii wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I continuely get told by everyone but rangers to snare mobs both in ldon and hunting outside.  Never by any means root them?  I just don't understand, I pull with snare they get close and i feel i should root them...  Makes sense to me no running mobs.  Had one run the other nite in an adventure, then got yelled at for not rooting, only response was "you told me never root, hence spell isnt memmed."  Am i wrong or what? Let me know all wise ones.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Tell them to do their own damn job and quit worrying about you. 
<br />

<br />
SNARE:
<br />
I snare the mobs that I know will flee when low on health.  Most NRO LDoN runs flee.  
<br />

<br />
#1
<br />
Pet Peeve - || %t || is ensnared 
<br />
The stupid MT is still beating on the damn thing and not pulling the next mob when the mob is trying to get away with snare.  Costs a Lil time which is not good in Slaughters. 
<br />

<br />
#2
<br />
Pet Peeve - || %t || is ensnared
<br />
The mob turns around which isnt gonna go anywhere cause it is ENSNARED/SNARED.   Stupid cleric casts ROOT.  Thing turns around and starts beating on everyone. 
<br />

<br />
ROOT:
<br />
I only use this for the following cases.
<br />
#1
<br />
Oh crap train!!  Bad pull.  Ill be rooting/snaring each mob so the rest of the crew can flee.
<br />
#2
<br />
Monk Splits.  He FDs and there are 2.  Instead of waiting for 1 to run off and tag we just root 1 mob and beat the crap outta of it.  If have enchanter with us - he/she will mez the rooted mob. 
<br />
#3
<br />
Breaking MEZ.  If the enchanter has the mob rooted I will root so the damn thing doesnt run off and smack the enchanter.  Dont know how many times ive seen the tank say ill taunt it - then whack whack whack enchanter @ 50% health.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I will only root with enchanter if I get.  Help help a %t is trying to take advantage of my C.<br />_________________<br />Better you than me.
