			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Good advice here -- snare and root are used for different reasons in different circumstances. Snare is almost always better than root for fleeing MOBs, if it will stick; nonetheless, some form of root is ALWAYS memmed on my ranger.
<br />

<br />
Small point, but it's important to clarify -- not all MOBs will flee. In fact not all N Ro LDoN MOBs will flee, at least in level 65 adventures. The rocks that are immune to root/snare don't flee, nor do the MOBs that enrage at low health. They'll all fight to the death. Point is, learn which MOBs flee and which don't -- avoid being summoned unnecessarily and save your group downtime.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/ytrill/ytrill8.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27521" target="_blank" class="postlink">Hunter Ytrill Stonebow</a>
