			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just adding a bit here.
<br />

<br />
Since you are only 44 you need to keep a couple of things in mind while readingt the above posts.
<br />

<br />
1) You do not have ensare yet.  You have snare which does not last nearly as long so if you are snaring when the mob is being pulled you need to re-snare when the mob is at 30-40 heath.  Having Tangling Weeds memmed is also a good idea.  If snare drops and the mob begins to run TW has an ultra fast cast rate (only lasts about 30-60 secs but thats enough to take the mob down).
<br />

<br />
2) At your level the root you have does damage.  Now I'm not sure - but I don't think that a chanter will be able to mez a mob that you have rooted.  Would someone please correct me if I am wrong.  So if I am right, if you are in a group with a chanter do not root any MOBs unless chanter calls for help.  (exception to this rull is casting root to break mez as noted above).
<br />

<br />
As for MOBs that flee.  In the BBM adventures nothing flees except the animal type MOBs (ie. the spiders, rats, spinners and crabby things).  In my experience nothing else runs.  However, my practice is to snare these guys anyway just in case a caster gets agro - as it gives Tank an extra second or two to regain agro.
<br />

<br />
I usually have TW, Ensnare and Root memmed at all times.  You never know when you will need them.<br />_________________<br />Cylest - Wood Elf Ranger of the 55th Summer
<br />
Tunare server
<br />

<br />
Insilium, defensors fidei</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
