				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Ytrill wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>TinyTank wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">At your level the root you have does damage.  Now I'm not sure - but I don't think that a chanter will be able to mez a mob that you have rooted.  Would someone please correct me if I am wrong.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
A chanter can mez a MOB after it's rooted. The problem occurs when the mez lands first. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Aye, I often ask Chantys to give me a moment to root mobs before they mez. That way if mez breaks the chanter doesnt get nailed while I am attacking the main mob. Since Chantys don't last long it can be tough to save them before they go down.
<br />
Also found that a good way to break mez is to root while MT stands right in front of the mob. This keeps the formerly mezzed mobs from agroing the chanty before the MT can get agro. And less dead mezzers are always a good thing.
<br />

<br />
As for snare vs root, I keep both spells memmed in every spell set except my buff sets. I snare every mob unless I am sure it wont run away (exp: undead are a waste of mana to snare, most undead don't ever run) or someone else is handling snares. I only root if the mob needs to be parked and will often nuke to break root before it gets to low Hp so snare can do its job.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=883781" target="_blank" class="postlink">Solael Evylsbane</a>, 58th Season Ranger of Karana,
<br />
Proud Council Member of <a href="http://www.qeynosguardians.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Qeynos Guardians</a>
<br />
<img src="http://members.cox.net/solael3/CritHigh.JPG" border="0" />
<br />
Karana Server</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
